column7: Restraint enforcement, whether adult seat belts or child safety seats, is a primary police function.
Most manufacturers allow child safety seats to be used with an automatic belt system.
Rear-facing seats can be installed in front of active airbags.
Latch plate is the only type of locking device on seat belt systems.
Child safety seats can be used in the rear of a law enforcement vehicle.
Select the appropriate questions to ask when placing a child in a car seat.
According to the International Association of Chiefs of Police model for enforcement, officers should address restraint issues on every traffic stop regardless of the original infraction.
